				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The -LATCH pulses with duration on the order of 10000 µs are probably a wait just less than a frame, as 16640 µs = 1 NTSC NES frame. The +LATCH pulses on the order of 1000 µs are probably just a couple thousand CPU cycles, just long enough to show that it's not a regular controller.
<br />
<br />It'd be possible to make a timing circuit to clean up clock signal distortions caused by the DPCM channel's DMA unit, much like the timing circuit in the MMC3's scanline counter that spreads A12 pulses. I wonder whether the glove has one.</div>

